pausing his glance long upon Daggoo, Queequeg, Tashtego; but shunning Fedallah; 
and then settling his firm relying eye upon the chief mate, said,—“Take the 
rope, sir—I give it into thy hands, Starbuck.” Then arranging his person in 
the basket, he gave the word for them to hoist him to his perch, Starbuck being 
the one who secured the rope at last; and afterwards stood near it. And thus, 
